### The Grasp

Reach, close hand (simulate with rotation), retract:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'arm (x 0))
  (entity 'hand (rotation 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'arm 'x 0 100 0.3 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.3
      (ease 'hand 'rotation 0 90 0.15 'cubic-in))
    (at 0.45
      (hold 0.1))
    (at 0.55
      (ease 'arm 'x 100 10 0.4 'cubic-in))))
```

[VISUAL: Arm extends, hand rotates (closing), pauses briefly, arm retracts with hand closed.]

The hand rotation at full extension is the *grasp*. The retract with closed hand is \"I have it.\"

