### The Recoil

Pull back sharply from something unpleasant. Entire upper body involved:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'torso (x 0))
  (entity 'head (rotation 0))
  (entity 'arm (x 0 y 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'torso 'x 0 -35 0.12 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 8 0.12 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'arm 'x 0 -40 0.12 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'arm 'y 0 10 0.12 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.12
      (hold 0.25))
    (at 0.37
      (ease 'torso 'x -35 -15 0.5 'cubic-in)
      (ease 'head 'rotation 8 3 0.5 'cubic-in)
      (ease 'arm 'x -40 -20 0.5 'cubic-in)
      (ease 'arm 'y 10 5 0.5 'cubic-in))))
```

[VISUAL: Torso, head, and arm pull back together, hold, then settle in a wary posture.]

The partial return (torso to -15, not 0) is *maintaining distance*. The head rotation away adds aversion.

