### The Lean-In

Forward motion, slow and deliberate. Interest, curiosity:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'torso (x 0 rotation 0))
  (entity 'head (y 0 rotation 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'torso 'x 0 30 0.7 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'torso 'rotation 0 5 0.7 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'y 0 5 0.7 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 -3 0.7 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.7
      (hold 1.0))))
```

[VISUAL: Torso shifts forward and tilts slightly, head extends and tilts down, long hold.]

The slow ease (0.7 seconds) is *deliberate interest*. The long hold is sustained attention.

---


### The Lean-Back

Opposite of lean-in. Skepticism, discomfort:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'torso (x 0 rotation 0))
  (entity 'head (rotation 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'torso 'x 0 -25 0.5 'cubic-out)
