### The Confident Stride Prep

Before walking, a weight shift and arm position—readiness:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'torso (x 0 rotation 0))
  (entity 'left-arm (rotation 0))
  (entity 'right-arm (rotation 0))
  (entity 'head (rotation 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'torso 'x 0 8 0.3 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'torso 'rotation 0 -3 0.3 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'left-arm 'rotation 0 15 0.3 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'right-arm 'rotation 0 -20 0.3 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 2 0.3 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.3
      (hold 0.4))))
```

[VISUAL: Torso shifts forward and rotates slightly, arms swing to stride-ready positions, head tilts slightly, holds.]

The shift and arm positions *precede* walking—anticipation.

