### The Cautious Stride Prep

Slow shift, arms closer to body, head lower:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'torso (x 0 y 0 rotation 0))
  (entity 'head (y 0 rotation 0))
  (entity 'left-arm (rotation 0))
  (entity 'right-arm (rotation 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'torso 'x 0 5 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'torso 'y 0 5 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'torso 'rotation 0 5 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'y 0 3 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 8 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'left-arm 'rotation 0 5 0.6 'cubic-out)
      (ease 'right-arm 'rotation 0 -5 0.6 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.6
      (hold 0.5))))
```

[VISUAL: Torso shifts forward slowly and lowers slightly, head dips, arms swing minimally, holds.]

The slow ease (0.6 seconds), lowered torso, and minimal arm swing are *caution*.

