### The Double-Take

Look, return, then snap back to look again with emphasis:

```scheme
(motion
  (entity 'head (rotation 0 y 0))
  (timeline
    (at 0.0
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 -30 0.2 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.2
      (hold 0.1))
    (at 0.3
      (ease 'head 'rotation -30 0 0.2 'cubic-in))
    (at 0.5
      (hold 0.15))
    (at 0.65
      (ease 'head 'rotation 0 -45 0.12 'back-out)
      (ease 'head 'y 0 -5 0.12 'cubic-out))
    (at 0.77
      (hold 0.5))))
```

[VISUAL: Head turns left, returns, pauses, then snaps left again with overshoot and slight pull-back.]

The second turn uses `back-out` (overshoot) and adds a y-displacement—*wait, what?!*

